summary: Me: I really like how Agrretsuko handled the topic of marriage and how even though it isn't for everyone, it's perfectly ok to...
body:
Me: I really like how Agrretsuko handled the topic of marriage and how even though it isn’t for everyone, it’s perfectly ok to desire it, never making Retsuko seem as a needy and “outdated” person for wanting to marry, as well as how it is respectful to people who do not want to marry themselves since it is a huge step that requires both parts to work. Maybe Retsuko’s standarts for love are a bit high, but they’re not impossible (one may even say, they’re the bare minimum), but I really like how the show didn’t force her to marry out of pity or to live in a relationship that was going were she didn’t actually want to go.

Also me:

summary: Tadano with a shy bunny s/o!! Please and thank you!!! 💞
question: Tadano with a shy bunny s/o!! Please and thank you!!! 💞
answer:
tadano is such a cool dude

  • i mean as it stands, retsuko was low key kind of shy, too. in other words, tadano has dealt with this sort of relationship before.
  • tadano love love lovesss your ears. big ear gang and all that jazz
  • he’s never gonna force you into something that you don’t want to do! this obviously stands for everyone he goes out with, but you know. if you don’t want to join him on his business socialite affairs, then he won’t get offended. if you just want to have a quiet night in, he’s your guy.
  • he loves the hight difference, ngl.
  • there’s a whole lotta fluff to love!
